YOUNG OWEN
What grade are you in?
MADDY
(while reading)
...Ninth.
She finishes the sentence she's reading, then glances over
briefly at Owen from across the lunch room, as if assessing
him.
MADDY (CONT'D)
What about you?
YOUNG OWEN
Seventh.
She snorts in quick laughter.
MADDY
Oh my gosh. You're a baby.
Owen looks down at the linoleum, ashamed.
Maddy notices and feels bad. So she tries to change the
subject.
MADDY (CONT'D)
--Election night is cool, right?
It's like Colonial Day, or when
they bring in the inflatable
planetarium to the gymnasium.
Owen nods, not really following her train of thought but
