      14.
YOUNG OWEN
My dad doesn't let me stay up that
late. 10pm's my bedtime.
MADDY
Damn. That absolutely sucks.
He looks down at the ground, embarrassed again.
MADDY (CONT'D)
My mom basically doesn't give a
shit when I go to bed.
Maddy looks at Owen as Owen sulks. A bad idea starts to form
in her head. She grins.
MADDY (CONT'D)
Hey: you know what you should do?
Owen looks up, on pins and needles for what Maddy might say
next...
18 INT. BRENDA'S CAR - NIGHT 18
Owen lays in the backseat of his mom's car, driving home from
election night. Streetlights reflect through the window and
dance across his face.
YOUNG OWEN
...Mom?
Owen tries to catch his mom's eyes in the rear view.
YOUNG OWEN (CONT'D)
Can I sleepover at Johnny Link's
house Saturday night?
BRENDA
Johnny Link? I didn't know you guys
were friends anymore.
Owen doesn't respond. He just waits for an answer.
Brenda considers the request...
BRENDA (O.S.) (CONT'D)
You'll need to ask your father.
Beat. Silence.
YOUNG OWEN
Can you ask him for me?
