Happy birthday to you. Happy
birthday to you.
Owen is singing with them, but he looks like he's not even
sure where he is, like this whole thing is a dream he's
sleepwalking through.
The employee with the cake sets it down in front of the
Birthday Boy.
FUN CENTER EMPLOYEES (CONT'D)
(singing)
Happy birthday, dear Charlie.
Owen stops singing in the middle of this line, as if he's
just had a flash of deja vu.
100.
    

p. 102
